Approximately 27 thousand females between the ages of 10 and 24 have been affected by sexual assault within a year. They have attended their medical checkups and emotional counselling to recover from their verbal as well as physical abuse. Many times, sexual abuse leads to abortion that is carried without any medical warrant.

Women who have been raped or become victims of sexual assault find it highly challenging to continue the pregnancy. Moreover, it is risky not only for their physical health, but for their mental health as well.

Moreover, if their partner or the family thinks they have had an abortion for recreational reasons, they can be faced with strong discrimination and stigma.

Dangers of Semen Intoxication

According to licensed counsellors and sexuality specialists, having semen inside an individual’s mouth can cause serious health problems. However, there is no such report that is based on scientific evidence.

More than 15 years ago, there was a case reported in an American English journal that claimed semen intoxication. Though not the genuine case, the report appeared in the two renal and urology journals and claimed that the semen can cause severe damage to an individual’s oral health as well as kidneys by prompting severe diabetes and hypertension.
